<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-13T12:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-13T12:36:00-05:00" n="954" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d954">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/13770.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Silliman</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-13T11:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 13, 1914, 11 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Generally speaking the Carranza generals appear to have allied themselves
                            with him yesterday as against the Convention on the presumption that
                            Villa will not be eliminated. Convention appears to have committed
                            itself to Villa, appointing him Commander-in-Chief, and has declared
                            Carranza in rebellion.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>